  "original_title": "\u2018\u0d9a\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0ddd\u0db1\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dcf \u0dc5\u0db8\u0dcf \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dcf\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'Child labor has increased due to Corona'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Labor Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said that with the covid epidemic, the trend of employing children as laborers in various professions has increased.",
        "The minister also said that laws will be brought to completely stop the use of child labor as well as the trafficking of children to earn money.",
        "The minister also mentioned that child and labor laws and ordinances should be amended for that.",
        "The minister said that the time has come to review the dangerous occupational regulations under the Women, Youth and Child Employment Act and informed the relevant authorities to give him suggestions on the amendments to be made to the Act.",
        "Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva said this in a discussion held at the Ministry of Labor yesterday (30).",
        "The Minister said that although some interpret the cause of child labor as the poverty of the parents, it is illegal to employ minor children and use them to earn money, and parents who are addicted to drugs mostly commit this crime.",
        "The minister said that people who use children for money-making activities should be arrested and dealt with according to the law."
      ],
